Chesser sanitizes HTML in move text. Only the following tags and attributes are preserved:

<pre><code>ALLOWED_TAGS = {{
&nbsp; "b", "i", "u", "em", "strong",
&nbsp; "a", "hr", "br", "ul", "ol", "li",
&nbsp; "code", "pre", "blockquote",
&nbsp;"fenseq",
}}
ALLOWED_ATTRIBUTES = {{
&nbsp; "a": {"href", "title"},
&nbsp; "fenseq": {"data-fen"},
}}
</code></pre>

Here we‚Äôre using the ‚Äúpreformatted‚Äù <code>&lt;pre&gt;</code> block and <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> inline tags.

Chesser normalizes spacing between paragraphs, HTML elements, and subvariations.

This guide covers all built-in HTML tags. The custom <code>&lt;fenseq&gt;</code> tag is covered in <a href="/variation/2/?idx=2">another guide</a>.

Black has now an opportunity to take the initiative that should not be wasted.

(4...Bc5 {(Classical Variation) attacks White‚Äôs central Knight on d4 and forces White to either move it or protect it. Black should expect replies like} 5.Be3{,} 5.Nxc6{, or} 5.Nb3).

(4...Nf6) {(Schmidt Variation) is a common alternative. Black puts immediate attacking pressure on White‚Äôs e-pawn.}

(4...Qh4) {(Steinitz Variation) is more aggressive. Black immediately attempts to win White‚Äôs e-pawn outright and indeed can practically win it by force. However, doing so costs time and White is thought to get more than enough compensation after:}

(4...Qh4 5.Nc3 Bb4 6.Be2 Qxe4 7.Nb5 Bxc3+ 8.bxc3 Kd8 9.O-O)

{No hesitation: We‚Äôre aiming to knock out White‚Äôs e-pawn! I began playing the Scandinavian Defense (also known as the ‚ÄúCenter Counter‚Äù) some 25+ years ago as a scholastic player in my native Minnesota.

A local master, FM Leonard Johnson, often seemed to obtain effortlessly good positions with this opening, and I thought ‚ÄúHey, why can‚Äôt I do that too?‚Äù :)

The ‚ÄúScandi‚Äù has served me well over the years, and in 2025 I published a mammoth 225,000+ word course about the opening on <a href="https://chessiverse.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chessiverse.com</a> called ‚Äú<a href="https://chessiverse.com/courses/scandi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The Comprehensive Scandinavian: A Complete Repertoire Based on 3...Qa5</a>.‚Äù}
